<doc id="188742" wikidata="Q1450336" url="?curid=188742" title="841 BC">
<text>The year 841 BC, is highly significant in ancient Chinese history, in that Sima Qian was able to construct a year-by-year chronology back to that point. Any earlier events in Chinese history cannot be confidently dated by historians.

== Events ==
* The in Western Zhou dynasty. The Chinese people rioted against King Li of Zhou, who was then sent to exile at a place called Zhi.
* The start of Gonghe Regency, an interregnum period in Chinese history, after King Li of Zhou was exiled.
* The First Assyrian Invasion of Israel.

== Births ==
== Deaths ==
* Marquis Jing of Jin, the sixth ruler of the state of Jin.
* Baal-Eser II, king of Tyre.

